				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Ganja Card Game" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The Ganja card game allows people to socialize while also learning about the biology and perils of farming weed (Cannabis sativa). Players have fun growing your garden and protecting it from aphids to male plants!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts 4 cards. Players take turns drawing one card from the deck and putting one card into play. Each play, you will have a choice or planting, or using an action card to slow down the progress of your competitors. The goal is to grow your garden by placing a female plant card in front of you, face up so that all can see. To close a round simply put down 6 female plant cards in your garden, the person who grows the most plants wins the game. If you want a longer game simply tally points over three rounds. Action cards are available to slow your competitors while teaching everyone about the biology and perils of farming weed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;      Male plants can be placed in a competitor's garden. If that player doesn't hold, draw or trade a &amp;quot;Gardener&amp;quot;, then their whole crop will be lost.&amp;#10;      Kangaroos steal the largest plant card&amp;#10;      Deer eat/destroy the largest plant card&amp;#10;      Aphids destroy the smallest plant card each turn unless &amp;quot;Ladybugs&amp;quot; are used, or no cards remain&amp;#10;      Ladybug card eats one &amp;quot;Aphid&amp;quot; card&amp;#10;      Edibles can be given to another player, and they will skip a turn&amp;#10;      Raided: the legal limit is 4 weed plants, so give this card to a competitor and they will skip a turn, and loose all but 4 plants&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
